@startuml "LLM Integration - Abstraction and Rendering"
title "LLM Integration: Client Abstraction and Response Rendering"

' LLM Client Abstraction
package "LLM Client Layer" {
  struct LLMRequest {
    + query: String
    + context: Option<String>
  }

  struct LLMResponse {
    + text: String
    + metadata: Option<serde_json::Value>
  }

  interface LLMClientTrait <<interface>> {
    + query(text: &str): Result<String>
    + query_with_context(text, context): Result<String>
    + query_with_history(text, history): Result<String>
  }

  note right of LLMClientTrait
    **Trait-Based Abstraction**
    Allows different implementations:
    - MockLLMClient (testing)
    - HttpLLMClient (production)
    - Future: OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.

    **Methods**
    - query(): basic query
    - query_with_context(): add context
    - query_with_history(): with command history
  end note
}

' Implementation: HTTP Client
package "HTTP Client Implementation" {
  class HttpLLMClient {
    - base_url: String
    - client: reqwest::Client
    --
    + new(base_url: String): Self
    + with_timeout(base_url, timeout_secs): Result<Self>
    + query(text: &str): Result<String>
    + query_with_context(text, context): Result<String>
  }

  note right of HttpLLMClient
    **Production Implementation**
    - REST API client via reqwest
    - 30-second timeout (default)
    - Supports custom timeouts (M2/M3)
    - JSON serialization

    **Error Handling**
    - Network timeouts
    - HTTP error codes
    - Malformed responses
    - Connection failures

    **Future Integration**
    - Endpoint and auth TBD
    - Backend selection pending
  end note

  HttpLLMClient ..|> LLMClientTrait : implements
}

' Implementation: Mock Client
package "Mock Client Implementation" {
  class MockLLMClient {
    - responses: HashMap<String, String>
    --
    + new(): Self
    + with_response(query, response): Self
    + add_response(query, response): void
    + query(text: &str): Result<String>
  }

  note right of MockLLMClient
    **Testing Implementation**
    - Predictable responses
    - No network calls
    - Fast test execution
    - Configurable behavior

    **Usage in Tests**
    - NaturalLanguageOrchestrator tests
    - Integration tests
    - Workflow simulations
  end note

  MockLLMClient ..|> LLMClientTrait : implements
}

' Response Rendering
package "Response Rendering" {
  class ResponseRenderer {
    + format_markdown(text: &str): String
    + highlight_code(code: &str, language: &str): String
    + format_inline(text: &str): String
    + render_line(line: &str): String
    --
    # parse_code_block(text): Vec<CodeBlock>
    # extract_language(fence_meta): String
  }

  struct CodeBlock {
    + language: String
    + code: String
    + start_line: usize
  }

  note right of ResponseRenderer
    **M1 Scope: Basic Markdown**
    Supported:
    - Code blocks with syntax highlighting
    - Inline code (backticks)
    - Bold (**text**)
    - Italic (*text*)
    - Lists (basic)

    **Not Yet (M2/M3)**
    - Tables
    - Images
    - Complex layouts
    - LaTeX math
  end note

  class SyntaxHighlighter {
    + highlight(code: &str, language: &str): String
    + get_available_languages(): Vec<&str>
    - apply_ansi_colors(token, color): String
  }

  note right of SyntaxHighlighter
    **Supported Languages (M1)**
    - rust
    - python
    - bash/shell
    - json
    - yaml
    - javascript/typescript
    - html/xml

    **Implementation**
    - Uses syntect crate
    - ANSI color codes
    - Terminal-compatible output
  end note

  ResponseRenderer --> SyntaxHighlighter : uses for code
  ResponseRenderer --> CodeBlock : parses
}

' Orchestrator Integration
class NaturalLanguageOrchestrator {
  - llm_client: Box<dyn LLMClientTrait>
  - renderer: ResponseRenderer
  --
  + query_llm(text: &str): Result<String>
  + format_response(response: &str): String
  + render_to_terminal(formatted: &str): String
}

note right of NaturalLanguageOrchestrator
  **Workflow**
  1. Receive NL input from classifier
  2. Prepare context (optional)
  3. Query LLM client
  4. Receive response text
  5. Parse markdown
  6. Apply syntax highlighting
  7. Format for terminal
  8. Display to user

  **Error Handling**
  - LLM errors: display error message
  - Format errors: fallback to plain text
  - Rendering errors: sanitize output
end note

NaturalLanguageOrchestrator --> LLMClientTrait : queries
NaturalLanguageOrchestrator --> ResponseRenderer : formats with

' Request/Response Flow
package "Request/Response Flow" {
  rectangle "User Input\n'how do I...'" as req1
  rectangle "Query LLM\n(with context)" as req2
  rectangle "Parse Response\nMarkdown" as req3
  rectangle "Syntax Highlight\nCode Blocks" as req4
  rectangle "Format for\nTerminal" as req5
  rectangle "Display\nOutput" as req6

  req1 --> req2 : NL input
  req2 --> req3 : LLMResponse
  req3 --> req4 : Parsed MD
  req4 --> req5 : Highlighted
  req5 --> req6 : ANSI colored
}

' Error Handling
package "Error Handling" {
  note as error_note
    **LLM Errors**
    - Network timeout: "Connection timeout"
    - HTTP error: "Service error (500)"
    - Malformed response: "Invalid response format"

    **Rendering Errors**
    - Invalid syntax highlight: fallback to plain text
    - Malformed markdown: best-effort parsing
    - Terminal size issues: wrap/truncate gracefully

    **User Experience**
    - Clear error messages
    - Fallback to plain text
    - Suggest retry if transient
  end note
}

' Integration with TerminalState
class TerminalState {
  + output: OutputBuffer
  + mode: TerminalMode
}

enum TerminalMode {
  WaitingLLM
  Normal
}

NaturalLanguageOrchestrator --> TerminalState : updates mode
NaturalLanguageOrchestrator --> OutputBuffer : adds formatted output

note bottom
  **LLM Integration Architecture**

  **Design Patterns**
  - **Trait Abstraction**: LLMClientTrait for multiple implementations
  - **Dependency Injection**: Client passed to orchestrator
  - **Strategy Pattern**: Different render strategies (M2/M3)
  - **Error Handling**: Graceful fallbacks

  **Future Extensions (M2/M3)**
  - OpenAI GPT API
  - Anthropic Claude API
  - Azure OpenAI Service
  - Local LLM (llama.cpp)
  - Streaming responses
  - Context history (command history, file context)
  - Custom system prompts
end note

@enduml
